First do this (skip "Preparation from Source" section including subsections):
https://kb.ettus.com/Software_Development_on_the_E310_and_E312#Preparation_using_PyBOMBS
Don't worry about "Compiling and installing UHD" because pybombs does this.

---------- NOTE!
Remember to always run the following before compiling anything:
source ~/prefix/setup_env.sh
source ~/prefix/environment-setup-armv7ahf-vfp-neon-oe-linux-gnueabi

----------
For ADSB:
cd ~/prefix/src
git clone https://github.com/bistromath/gr-air-modes.git
mkdir gr-air-modes/build
cd gr-air-modes/build
cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr -DENABLE_E300=ON ..
make -j4
make install DESTDIR=~/prefix
rsync ~/prefix ...

----------
To talk to the USRP via ethernet:
sudo ip link set enp0s25 up
sudo ip addr add 10.101.10.1/24 dev enp0s25
sudo systemctl start dnsmasq
ssh root@10.101.10.11
And in reverse:
sudo systemctl stop dnsmasq
sudo ip addr del 10.101.10.1/24 dev enp0s25
sudo ip link set enp0s25 down

----------
TO RUN ON USRP:
Run the commands from "Running the new UHD via sshfs"

